# Remnants of Faerun: Homebrew Subclasses
Since the dawn of the new world, built on the ruins of faerun, new creatures, magic, and feats from indivuals are discovered every day. These individuals carve their name into the tomes of history through their new achievements or ability and strength.

## Barbarian
The people called savages or brutes by the everyday person ignore their scoffs and looks of distain, for they know that the fits of aggression they fear, are the boons of nature. And what is nature, but chaos. These Primal Paths represent the newfound power that some indiviuals have found themselves able to access.

### Path of the Savage Beast
Born in nature, you were raised by and learned from its creatures. Their example leads to your survival, their power an inspiration. After a while you unlocked the potential within yourself to embody them in aspects beyond normal capabilities. Their spirit fills you and grants you their abilities and strength. You lead your life with the instincts and prowess of the beast, making you more dangerous than others could comprehend.

#### Feral Origins
At 3rd level, you choose a Primal Beast that speaks to you inner animal from the Primal Beast table. You gain Beast Claws (2d4+1 damage) to replace your unarmed strikes. The nature of your beast claws depends on your Primal Beast. For any saving throws creatures have to make against your Primal Beast abilities, use (DC 8 + your Strength modifier + your proficiency bonus). So long as you have a free hand, you can use your bonus action to make an attack with your Beast Claws. These Beast Claws are usable while in Rage.

At 5th level, your Beast Claws increase to 3d4+1 damage. At 10th level, your Beast Claws increase to 4d4+1 damage.


#### Beast Habits
At 3rd level, when you adopt this path, you gain the following benefits when in the home terrain of your beast.
Gain Advantage on Wisdom skill checks
Be able to speak to creatures as if you were using the Speak with Animals spell
Increase your movement speed by 5 feet
Ignore non-magical difficult terrain

```
```



Primal Beast
--
| Beast | Terrain | Abilities |
|-------|---------|-----------|
|Aboleth|Underdark|Your Beast Claws do bludgeoning damage with a reach of 10 feet|
|Bear|Forest|Your Beast Claws do slashing damage and your hit point maximum increases by 1 per level of Barbarian|
|Bison|Grassland|Your Beast Claws do slashing damage and you choose a Draconic Imitant. When raging, gain resistance to the appropriate Damage type related to your imitant.|
|Crocodile|Swamp|Your Beast Claws do piercing damage and you gain a swim speed equal to your movement speed|
|Desert Fox|Desert|Your Beast Claws do bludgeoning damage and you can perform Charge from the Giant Boar in the Monster Manual|
|Dragon|Mountain|Your Beast Claws do piercing damage and can take the Dash action as a bonus action|
|Shark|Coast/Ocean|Your Beast Claws do piercing damage and you gain advantage on all grapple checks and deal +1 bonus damage to grappled opponents|
|Wolf|Arctic|Your Beast Claws do piercing damage and you gain the Pack Tactics Feat from the Wolf in the Monster Manual|

<div class='pageNumber'>1</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | BARBARIAN</div>



\page

#### Feral Rage
Starting at 6th level, your rage becomes even more primal than before, preventing you from ending your rages early so long as you are aware of danger to yourself. While raging, as a bonus action, you can unleash a roar that induces fear. All hostile creatures within a 30 foot radius must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, they become frightened. They can reattempt their saving throw at the end of each of their turns. Once a creature saves, they are immune to this roar for 1 hour. You can use this ability once per long rage.

Additionally, your Beast Claws now count as magical for the sake of overcoming resistances and immunities.

### Transformation
At 10th level, You can expend additional charges of Rage as an action to assume a rage form that polymorphs you into a were-creature or half-creature of your Primal Beast.
For each charge of Rage you expend beyond 1, you transform your body. You remain changed for 1 minute per charge and gain 5 temporary hit points per charge. This transformation does not affect your alignment.

Using the Beast stat block from the Monster Manual, if any of your ability scores would increase, apply the changes for the duration. If they would decrease, use your original scores instead. This does not affect your hit points, AC, or actions beyond what is granted. While in this form of rage, you disarm yourself at the time of transformation and only can use Beast Claws to attack. you also gain the ability listed in the Transformation Tier 1 Table.

```
```

Transformation Tier 1
--
| Beast | Monster Stat Block | Abilities |
|-------|--------------------|-----------|
|Aboleth|Aboleth|Once per day, target a creature you can see within 30 feet. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be magically charmed by you until it next takes damage from you or an ally. It can attempt another saving throw at the end of its subsequent turns.|
|Bear|Werebear|When you make a melee attack, you can have your target make a Strength saving throw  and on a fail, they are knocked back 10 feet and prone. Your hit point maximum and current hit points increase by your Barbarian level a second time upon transforming.|
|Bison|Giant Goat|If you move at least half your movement in a straight line, change your Beast Claws damage dice to d6’s and anyone you hit along your movement must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity.|
|Crocodile|Giant Crocodile|You gain +1 AC and a successful Beast Claws attack allows you to immediately grapple your target|
|Desert Fox|Weretiger|After moving 10 feet straight toward a target, make a Beast Claws attack. If you hit, the target must make a Strength saving throw. On a fail, you knock the target prone and the target has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end of its next turn.|
|Dragon|Half-Dragon|As an action, you can use the Dragonborn’s Breath Weapon 3x per Transformation based on your previously chosen Draconic Imitant.|
|Shark|Giant Shark|When you strike a creature with your Beast Claws, and start your next turn within 5 feet of them, You can attack them for another attack of Beast Claws as a free action. You can breath underwater and on land.|
|Wolf|Werewolf|Your movement speed increases by 10 feet and your Beast Claw attacks now heal you for half of the damage you inflict with them. If you are not missing any hit points, you can gain temporary hit points up to 10 from this ability|

Starting at 14th level, you gain an additional ability from the Transformation Tier 2 table when you
transform for your Transformation Rage based on your Primal Beast

