Transformation Tier 2
--
| Beast | Monster Stat Block | Abilities |
|-------|--------------------|-----------|
|Aboleth|Aboleth|Psychic Drain: As an action, one creature charmed by you takes 3d6 psychic damage, and you regain hit points equal to the damage the creature takes.|
|Bear|Werebear|You become a large creature and your Beast Claws now deal d6’s instead of d4’s for  damage.|
|Bison|Giant goat|Gorge: When you damage a creature with Beast Claws, they must make a Constitution saving throw or take 1d8 additional damage and be slowed until the end of their next turn.|
|Crocodile|Giant Crocodile|Grow a tail that acts as Beast Claws (bludgeoning) with a reach of 10 feet. This attack cannot target a creature grappled by you. A creature targeted by your tail must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.|
|Desert Fox|Weretiger|Maul: If a creature within 5 feet is prone, you can use your bonus action to make 2 Beast Claws attacks against them.|
|Dragon|Half-dragon|You gain Blindsight for 10 feet, Darkvision for 60 feet, and your Fly speed is now equal to half your movement speed.|
|Shark|Giant Shark|Blood Frenzy: You have advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature that is below its hit point maximum.|
|Wolf|Werewolf|Gain damage reduction 2d8 to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from non-magical attacks that aren’t silvered. |


