> ***Amphibious.*** The Lesser Kraken can breathe air and water.
>
> ***Freedom of Movement.*** The Lesser Kraken ignores difficult terrain, and magical effects can't reduce its speed or cause it to be restrained. It can spend 5 feet of movement to escape from non-magical restraints or being grappled..
>
> ***Multiattack.*** The Lesser Kraken makes three Tentacle attacks, each of which it can replace with one use of Fling.
> ### Actions
> ***Tentacle.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +7 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. *Hit* 1d6 + 4 (6) bludgeoning damage. If a creature is hit by this attack twice in one turn, the target is grappled (escape DC 15). Until this grapple ends, the target is restrained. The Lesser Kraken can grapple 2 targets at a time.
>
> ***Fling.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* One Medium or smaller object held or creature grappled by the Lesser Kraken is thrown up to 30ft. in a random direction and knocked prone. If a thrown target strikes a solid surface, the target takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage for every 10 feet it was thrown. If the target is thrown at another creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw (DC 15) or take the same damage and be knocked prone. 
>
> ***Ink Cloud.*** As an action while underwater, the kraken expels an ink cloud in a 20ft. radius. The cloud spreads around corners, and that area is heavily obscured to creatures other than the Lesser Kraken.  A strong current disperses the cloud, which otherwise disappears at the end of the kraken's next turn. This ability can only be used once before a long rest is needed to recharge it.

&nbsp;

### Circle of Spiritwalker’s
Druids of the Circle of Spiritwalker's commune with the spirits of the world, animal and humanoid alike. They are often leaders of their people, as they have a vast knowledge of traditions and history for their areas. Some act as keepers of the spirits of fallen animals, not yet ready to move on. They preserve the life of all their wards, through the knowledge of their existence, and respect for their afterlife. They are friendly to strangers, knowing that in the end, death treats all as equals

#### Knowledge Keeper
Starting at 2nd level when you choose this circle, your connection with the spirits of the world allows you insight to past events you or the have witnessed. You gain proficiency in the History skill. You may add double your proficiency bonus to history rolls you make.
Once per day, you may ask the spirits of the area you are in for their insight to the history of the land, granting you advantage on a history check.

#### Spiritual Guardianship
Beginning at 2nd level, you can summon forth a spirit of the land to aid an ally. As a bonus action. you may summon an animal spirit, a humanoid spirit, or a fey spirit to guard over a creature you can see and provide different boons. Only you see the spirits as they are, for others, it is a faint light that is slightly aloft the ground.

&nbsp;

**Animal:** Grant advantage on Dexterity and Wisdom saving throws

**Humanoid:** If the creature took the attack action, they can use their bonus action to make an additional attack. If the creature can already make an additional attack using their bonus action, this additional attack has advantage.

**Fey:** A hostile creature harmed by the creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be Feared of them. The creature also gains immunity to charm and sleep, ending any such effects at the time of being guarded.

&nbsp;

Any creature with a spirit guarding them has a +1 bonus to all saving throws. Spirits last for 1 minutes before disappearing, of if you become unconscious. If a creature would drop to 0 hit points or below while guarded by a spirit, you can use your reaction to instead have the spirit save them and instantly have them become stabilized once per long rest. Creatures can only be guarded by 1 spirit at a time.

You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier, and can have a maximum of 1 animal, 1 human, and 1 fey spirit called out at a time. All uses of this feature recharge on a long rest.

<div class='pageNumber'>12</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 3 | DRUID</div>

\page

#### Circle Spells
Your mystical connection to the spirits infuses you with the ability to cast certain spells. At 3rd, 5th, 7th, and 9th level you gain access to circle spells connected to the spirits you watch over.
Once you gain access to a circle spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn’t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day. If you gain access to a spell that doesn’t appear on the druid spell list, the spell is nonetheless a druid spell for you.

| Druid Level | Spells |
|-------|---------|
|3rd|Locate Animals or Plants, Warding Bond|
|5th|Speak with Dead, Spirit Guardians|
|7th|Death Ward, Divination|
|9th|Dominate Person, Reincarnate|

### Walk Among the Dead
At 6th level, while you are in Wild Shape, you can use your action to slip away into the Ethereal Plane for up to 1 minute. While there, you can navigate up to 60 feet away from the location you entered from, and choose to reappear as a bonus action. Additionally, any spirits you had active from Spiritual Guardianship grant their ward 1d6 tempoary hit points. Returning from the Ethereal Plane grants you advantage on your next attack roll, so long as the target could not percieve you while you were in the Ethereal Plane.

You can use this feature once per long rest.

At 14th level, you can use this feature an additional time per long rest.

### Otherworldly Visage
Beginning at 10th level, you can use your action to ask the spirits to help you watch your surroundings. The spirit combines with you, overtaking your vision with its own, giving you blindsense for 15 feet and advantage on Dexterity and Wisdom saving throws for 5 minutes. You can also choose as a bonus action to switch your vision over into viewing the Ethereal plane instead of the Material plane, and vice versa.

You also can move the spirit aiding you as if using the spell Arcane Eye, but cannot exceed past 30 feet from you or you lose your connection. You can use this feature 2 times, and all uses of this feature recharge on a long rest.

### Spectres of the World
Starting at 14th level, you can call for the phantoms of the land to aid you in your plight.

As an action, you summon 2 Guardian Ghost’s within 5 feet of you. They share your initiative and cannot move more than 15 feet away from you unless they are successful in using their Possession skill. They disappear after 5 minutes in the Material Plane. You can use this feature once per long rest.

