#### Spellcasting Ability
Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your spells. The power of your spells comes from your devotion to your practice. You use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.

&nbsp;


**Spell save DC** = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

&nbsp;


**Spell attack modifier** = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

```
```

#### Calming Vibes
At 6th level, You can use your action to grasp onto a hostile creature to calm it down and make it more difficult for it to get into the fighting spirit. The target creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your Spell save DC or be calmed. While calmed, the following effects take place.

* If the creature was in a state of Rage, that ends immediately and they are unable to re-enter a state of Rage until the end of your next turn.
* The creature has disadvantage on all attack rolls.
* The creature has disadvantage on all spell concentration checks.
* The creature is charmed to you and 1 ally within 5 feet.

You can use this feature on a non hostile creature without making an attack, and if they fail their saving throw, you have advantage on all Charisma checks against the target for the next hour. If they succeed, they are immune to this effect for 24 hrs.

You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier.

All uses of this feature recharge on a long rest.

<div class='pageNumber'>19</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 3 | MONK</div>
\page
#### Tranquil Stance
Starting at 11th level, So long as you have not moved during this round, you can use your action to close your eyes and enter a peaceful state of mind, making you aware of every creature's movements around you. While in this state, you gain the following traits:

* Your speed drops to 0
* You gain +3 to your AC, and an additional +1 to AC if you are below half of your hit points maximum
* You gain advantage on all saving throws. If you already had advantage for a saving throw from something besides this feature, gain a +2 bonus towards the saving throw instead.
* You gain blindsense for 10ft.

At 14th level, you heal yourself for 1d8 hit points for each failed attack made against you while in this stance.

These traits end at the start of your next turn. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier. All uses of this feature recharge on a long rest.

#### Peaceful ways
Starting at 17th level, once per long rest, you can focus all of your mind and natural energy into creating an atmosphere of peace.
As an action, spend a spell slot to target a number of creatures equal to the level of the spell slot used within 30 feet and target them all with Calming vibes.

If at least a 5th level spell slot was used, all chosen creatures have disadvantage on their saving throws.

If a creature rolls a 1-5 for their saving throw, they are charmed for 3 turns.

<div class='pageNumber'>20</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 4 | MONK</div>
\page

## Paladin

Through the ever changing creeds of man, so to do the deities who decide to take on new champions. Oaths taken with the solemn vow to uphold their beliefs and execute their will has created Paladins of a different caliber. Not all seek to quile the the ignorant, but are unafraid to do so should it be necessary for their cause. It truly is a new age of chosen acolytes.

### Oath of the Seeker

Paladins chosen for the Oath of Seeking pursue a quest set forth to them by their deity. It is always a trial since those personally selected by their deities are chosen for their skill or determination. This destiny is not always known though, and not all are a simple seeking of a truth to life. Some may be preparing for a great calamity to befall the land, and others might be looking for a lost temple before it is too late. No matter what the test, these paladins live a nomadic life, upholding their tenets all the while.

#### Tenents of Devotion
Though the exact words and strictures of the Oath of Seeking vary per path, paladins of this oath typically share these tenets.

&nbsp;


**Honesty.** Don’t lie or cheat. Let your word be your life and value it for the miralce it is.

&nbsp;


**Courage.** Never fear to act, as the brave will have what they wish out of life.

&nbsp;


**Honor.** Treat others with fairness, and let your honorable deeds be an example to them. Do as much good as possible while causing the least amount of harm. 

&nbsp;


**Truthseeker.** That the truth be revealed matters more than most things. Should a mystery present itself, it is your duty to shed light to its answer. 

&nbsp;


**Representative of the Scholar** The preservation and pursuit of knowledge is a noble endeavor, and should be aided when you find yourself able to.


#### Oath Spells
You gain oath spells at the paladin levels listed.

##### Oath of the Seeker Spells
| Paladin Level | Spells |
|:----:|:-------------|
| 3rd  | Bane, Comprehend Languages |
| 5th  | Crown of Madness, Zone of Truth |
| 9th  | Aura of Vitality, Tongues |
| 13th | Confusion, Locate Creature |
| 17th | Banishing Smite, Legend Lore |



#### Power of knowledge
Your Channel Divinity, Divine Sense, Spellcasting, Aura of Protection, and Cleansing Touch can use your Intelligence modifier instead of your Charisma modifier if you choose.

```
```

#### Channel Divinity
When you take this oath at 3rd level, you gain the following two Channel Divinity Options 

&nbsp;


**Sacred Weapon.** As an action, you can imbue one weapon that you are holding with positive energy, using your Channel Divinity. For 1 minute, you add your Intelligence modifier to attack rolls and damage rolls made with that weapon (with a minimum bonus of +1). The weapon also emits bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light 20 feet beyond that. If the weapon is not already magical, it becomes magical for the duration.
You can end this effect on your turn as part of any other action. If you are no longer holding or carrying this weapon, or if you fall unconscious, this effect ends.

&nbsp;


**Speaker for the Dead.** As an action, you present your Holy Symbol and speak a prayer for 1 minute to ask a spirit to share its knowledge with you. Using your channel divinity, you can cast the spell Speak with Dead to ask its name, where it calls home, and what killed it.

#### Knowledge of the Spirit
Starting at 7th level, when a friendly creature you can see makes an Intelligence Saving Throw, they can use your modifier instead of theirs. 

Additionally, 2 times per long rest when you cast a spell that forces another creature to make a Wisdom or Charisma saving throw, you can change that saving throw into an Intelligence saving throw. You can use this ability 2 times per long rest.

At 15th level, you now have 3 uses of this ability per long rest.

#### Attack on the Mind
Starting at 15th level, your psyche can attack others from a distance as you enlighten them to a truth they refuse to face themselves.

Whenever a creature you can see hits you with an attack, that creature takes psychic damage equal to your Intelligence modifier if you’re not incapatcitated.

If this feature activates, your AC increases by 1 until the start of your next turn.

#### Speaker of the Truth
At 20th level, your mind opens up to the planes as you learn all there is to know.

As an action, you can use this to cast any spell from the Clerics, Paladins, or Wizards spell list and add it to your spell list for 5 minutes. Intelligence becomes the spellcasting skill used for this spell. The spell is cast at a maximum of 5th level. You can use this feature once per long rest.

<div class='pageNumber'>21</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | PALADIN</div>
\page

### Oath of the Valkyrie

Valkyrie are among the most devoted of Paladins. Being a Valkyrie is to swear service to a god over life, death, and the transition between the two. They are the mightiest of champions who use their unworldly resilience to protect the sacredness of their deities domain. All Valkyrie gladly face their end on the field of battle than to idly stand by and be safe. The champions of the Valkyrie are granted steeds of lifelong companionship who share their bond with to carry out their justice and judgement.

#### Tenents of Devotion
Valkyrie tenants specifically carry from what deity they serve, but they ultimately uphold these shared vows.

&nbsp;


**From Life to Death.** The sacredness of life, and permanence of death is to be upheld. It is a one way road that all creatures travel, and abominations that go against the grain to be removed.

&nbsp;


**Unbroken.** As a sworn instrument of divine justice to your deity, you neve flee a battle, abandon a quest, and give any cause you devote yourself to your all

&nbsp;


**Noblest of Deaths.** To die in battle is the ultimate end to any Valkyrie, and it is welcomed with opened arms. As the natural order of the world, it is known that to die in a fight for your deities righteousness is the unequivocal prize of a life well lived.

&nbsp;


**Will of the People.** The call of the public is the responsibility of those in power to aid them.

#### Oath Spells
You gain oath spells at the paladin levels listed.

##### Oath of the Valkyrie Spells
| Paladin Level | Spells |
|:----:|:-------------|
| 3rd  | Compelled Duel, Zephyr Strike |
| 5th  | Enhance Ability, Lesser Restoration |
| 9th  | Haste, Remove Curse |
| 13th | Aura of Purity, Death Ward |
| 17th | Dispel Evil and Good, Greater Restoration |

#### Engulfed in Light
Your Channel Divinity, now exudes its own aura  of radiant power. Whenever you use a channel divinity, you and any creatures within 5 feet are healed for 1d8 hit points. If the creature is undead, it takes 1d8 radiant damage.

```
```

#### Channel Divinity
When you take this oath at 3rd level, you gain the following two Channel Divinity Options 

&nbsp;


**Compelling Spear** As an action, you can use your Channel Divinity to summon a holy spear of radiant light. The spear acts as a normal spear, but shatters upon successfully damaging a creature. A creature hit by this spear takes 4d6 radiant damage. If the target is undead, you can add a free use of the Searing Smite spell as part of the attack. If this spear is thrown and misses, as a reaction, you can teleport it back to your hand.

A spear can only last for 1 minute before disappearing. Ending your turn with the spear held by you hurts you for 1d4 radiant damage. When your spear would shatter after successfully harming a creature, roll 1d4, and on a 4, a new spear appears in your hand.

At 9th level, the damage increases to 4d6 Radiant damage. At 17th level, it increases again to 5d6 Radiant Damage.

&nbsp;


**Escort of Passing** You can use your Channel Divinity as an action to pray to your deity with your holy symbol and ask that you be able to bridge the living and dead to ferry those stuck between. Doing this allows you to sense any undead or see ghosts within 200 feet for 1 hour. Any ability checks or attack rolls made against creatures affected by this ability have advantage. Any undead revealed from this cannot divulge any information like the Speak with Dead spell would normally allow. Any slain undead, or ghosts convinced to move on to the otherside with a Wisdom (Religion) ability check pleases your deity and grant you 10 temporary hit points for 1 hour.

#### The Call of Valhalla
Starting at 7th level, when you fall below half of your hit point maximum, you and all allies within 15 feet gain 1d8+1 temporary hit points. At 18th level, the temporary hit points increase to 2d8+1. Once per short rest.

<div class='pageNumber'>22</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 2 | PALADIN</div>
\page

#### Steed of Devotion
Starting at 15th level, your deity acknowledges your growth and commitment to be amongst the highest of their followers and awards you a steed so that you may better carry out their divine agenda.

You may choose between the Pegasus or the Griffin listed below to be your steed. If you do not share a known language with your chosen mount, they learn one language that you know.

At 18th level, your chosen mount gains 15 more hit points.

You gain advantage on saving throws made to avoid falling off our mount. If you do fall off your mount and descend no more than 10 feet, you can land on your feet without taking damage if you are not incapacitated.

Should your mount die, you may perform the necessary burial ritual with 8 hours of intesnsive prayer and ask your deity to unite you with another companion to carry out their will. Roll 1d12 and a new mount will be granted to you in an amount of days equal to the result. If you are unable to give the proper burial rites to your fallen mount within 24 hours, the time is increased to 2d12.

___
> ## Pegasus
>*Large celestial, neutral good*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 13
> - **Hit Points** 39 (4d10+8)
> - **Speed** 60ft., Fly 60ft.
