> ___
> ***Haunting Flutter.*** This creature can use its action to hover around the head of a creature menacingly. The creature must make a DC 11 Wisdom saving throw to ignore the creature on it's turn, or lose its bonus action and reaction until the start of the Animated Skull's next turn. If the Animated skull is damaged while it is using Haunting Flutter, it no longer is pestering the creature.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Skull Bash.*** *Melee Attack:* +5 to hit, reach 5ft., one target. *Hit* 7 (1d6 + 1) The Animated Skull takes 1d4 bludgeoning damage whenever this attack succeeds

<div class='pageNumber'>32</div>
<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | SORCERER</div>
\page

#### Never Forgotten
At 14th level, you can try and scan the area to find a humanoid corpse buried beneath the earth. So long as you are on soft earth or swamp, as a bonus action, you can roll a d4 to see how many corpses or skeletons you are able to magically phase to the surface. Roll 1d4 to determine what happens as listed below:

1. You do not find any corpse or skeleton to raise up. 
2. You bring up 1 corpse or skeleton. 
3. You bring up 1 corpse or skeleton. 
4. You bring up 2 corpses or skeletons.

The DM can decide for a different type of corpse or skeleton other than humanoid to be brought up, but it is of a medium or smaller creature. These corpses or skeletons spawn within 10 feet of you, and Corpses or skeletons raised from this feature magically phase back into the ground where they originally were raised from after 1 minute of not being used in a spell, regardless of where they are at that time. This feature can only be performed once per short rest.

Furthermore, anytime you raise a creature using a spell, the raised creature now adopts your Dex. Modifier  and Cha. Modifier if yours is higher than the creatures original modifier, They also gain +2 to their AC, and 3 additional Hit Points per your Con. Modifier (Minimum of 1).

#### The Sanctity of Life
At 18th level, you can now combine essences into your raised minions and even fuse corpses together to make a true masterpiece of revival arcana.

As a bonus action, you can infuse one of your stored Essences into a creature raised with a spell and give it one of the following benefits. A creature can have each benefit used on it once, and cannot have the benefit reapplied again.

* Heal the creature for 2d8 hit points and give it 2d8 temporary hit points.
* Raise the creatures AC by +2 and give it +2 to its Str. Score, Dex. Score, and Cha. Score
* Increase the creatures speed by 10 feet, and grant the creature the ability to cast the spell Inflict Wounds one time at 1st level. It’s spell attack bonus is equal to yours for this casting.

You can also now fuse 2 corpses into a Fused Zombie or Fused Skeleton that has 2 heads, 4 arms, and 4 legs, or 3 corpses into a Greater Zombie or Greater Skeleton. When you use a spell to raise a corpse or skeleton, and another corpse or skeleton is within 5 feet of it, you can spend 1 additional spell slot of the same level to combine them into a Fused Zombie/Skeleton. If there are 3, you can spend 3 spell slots to combine them into a Greater Zombie/Skeleton. A fused creature is separated back into its original pieces whenever the effects of the spell that resurrected it end.

___
> ## Fused Zombie / Skeleton
>*Medium undead, Chaotic Neutral*
> ___
