### School of Force
The manifestation of arcana as a physcial force is not the most difficult thing to do, but maintaining it perfectly instead of having it be a fleeting single motion is art. Wizards of the School of Force are masters at manipulating the arcane energy around them to phase into a near solid force. This assists them in feats of extra protection, and even achieving improved strength for themselves. When the intangible becomes tangible, the possibilities open up to near infinite new avenues to explore.


#### Expertise in Force
Beginning when you select this school at 2nd level, the gold and time you must spend to copy a conjuration spell into your spellbook is halved.

#### Fist de Cuffs
Additionally at 2nd level, you gain the Improved Mage Hand cantrip, and it does not count against the number of cantrips you can know.

#### Protective Force
Starting at 6th level, Whenever you cast a Conjuration spell, a residual charge of magic protects you after the spells casting for 1 minute. This charge grants you a +1 to AC and, if an attack damages you, 1d4 damage mitigation. Upon taking damage, or 1 minute passing, the charge fades from you.

Should an attack that inflicts force damage target you while your AC is increased from a charge of this feature, your magic negates the force damage, adding an additional +1 to your AC to a maximum of +3 instead.

#### Handy Casting
Beginning at 10th level, You can now place your Improved Mage Hand over your own hands. When you do so, your Strength score increases by +2, and you have advantage on any Strength ability checks and saving throws. Any spell attacks you cast while your mage hand is over your own gains +1d4 force damage.


#### Fists of the Mage
Starting at 14th level, You can conjure 2 muscular Mage hands and arms over your own, and 2 others appear from your back and reach around to your front as a bonus action, glowing with intense power for 1 minute. While you have Fists of the Mage active, you add +2 to AC, your unarmed strikes gaint he following attributes:

* Have a reach of 10 ft.
* Gain a bonus +5 to hit
* Deal 2d4+Strength mod. Force damage.

You gain the Multiattack feature if you use the attack action to make an unarmed strike, allowing you to make 4 attacks with your unarmed strikes.

You also have advantage on all Strength saving throws or strength checks, and a temporary bonus of +3 to your Strength Score for those saving throws or checks.

If you are the sole target of a ranged spell attack while Fists of the Mage is active, you can make a Dexterity saving throw equal to 9 + the casters bonus to spell attacks to block it with your force hands to reduce the damage by half your Wizard level+2.

You can conjure Fists of the Mage 2 times. All uses of this feature recharge on a long rest.







\page




### School of Alchemy

#### Expertise in Chemistry
Beginning when you select this school at 2nd level, you gain proficiency with Alchemy tools and one other toolset of your choice, along with the Survival skill. You have advantage when trying to identify the effects of a potion or similar mixture. Creating potions with an alchemy kit allows you to add your proficiency bonus to any damaging or healing effects they include. Ingredients can be obtained at an alchemy shop, or by foraging in nature for 2 hours using a Survival skill check to find 10 gp worth of ingredients. You can only forage in an area once per day.


#### Hasty Concoction
Additionally at 2nd level, you can throw together ingredients quickly to get a potion of suitable effects, but you have to act fast. As an action, use 10gp worth of ingredients, to create a potion from the Hasty Concoction Potion Table.

The potion effects can only be activated within 1 minute after being created, and turns into a foul smelling mixture after that time that gives no additional effect. To make a potion, you must have an empty bottle, vial, or other suitable container. When you throw a potion, the potions are treated as Simple melee Weapons with a Thrown range of 15/30 feet.

Roll 1d20 to see which potion you create. If you instead spend 4 hours with an alchemy kit, you can select a specific potion to create from the list below whose effects stay eligible for activation for 8 hours.

#### Long Range Administration
Starting at 6th level, you gain proficiency with Hand crossbows, and can now fuse a Hasty Concoction potion into the tip of a crossbow bolt as a bonus action. This causes the next shot of that crossbow to apply the potion effect as part of the weapon attack if it hits. If the bolt is not used within 1 minute the effects fade.

If the potion effects an area, the target of the weapon attack roll becomes the source location for the potion effect to activate from regardless if the attack roll hit or not.

#### Efficient Chemistry
Beginning at 10th level, Any potions you craft that involve dealing damage or healing have their amount of dice doubled. Additionally, the cost of crafting potions is now cut to 5gp. If you still spend 10gp worth however, you can roll your Hasty Concoction feature with advantage and take either result.

#### Mad Doctor
Starting at 14th level, You can spend 1 hr, instead of 4 hours, to craft a potion that will last 24 hours instead of only 8. Additionally, you can fuse 2 separate potions together as an action by using your magic to keep them contained in the same container, but still independent of one another. This will activate both potions simultaneously whenever they are activated by drinking or by breaking.

Any potions you craft that involve dealing damage or healing now add your Intelligence modifier to their damage or healing.

\page
<div class='wide'>
##### Hasty Concoction Potion Table
| d20 | Potion | Effect |
|:----:|:-------------|:-------------|
| 1 | **Potion of Acid.** | If this potion is ingested, the target creature suffers 2d6 acid damage. If the potion is broken onto a surface or creatures, all creatures within 5’ of the target area are doused in the corrosive liquid. The creatures must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be hit for 2d6 acid damage. On a save, the creatures take half damage. |
| 2  | **Potion of Cleansing.** | If this potion is consumed, any conditions of Blinded, Charmed, Deafened, Frightened, Invisible, Paralyzed, or Poisoned are removed. If the potion is broken onto a creature, only Blinded, Invisibility, and Paralyzed conditions can be removed. |
| 3 | **Potion of Cold.** | If this potion is ingested, the target creature suffers 2d6 cold damage. If the potion is broken onto a surface or creatures, all creatures within 5’ of the target area are exposed to a freezing cold. The creatures must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be hit for 2d4 cold damage and be slowed until the start of your next turn. On a save, the creatures take half damage and are not slowed. |
| 4 | **Potion of Darkness.** | This potion absorbs light perfectly through the smoke cloud that rises from the liquid. If the potion is consumed, the target creature releases black puffs of smoke each time it breathes or speaks for 10 minutes. If the potion is broken on a creature or surface, a black smoke cloud appears in a 10 foot by 10 foot area and acts as if the spell Darkness was cast. |
| 5 | **Potion of Fire.** | If this potion is ingested, the target creature suffers 2d6 fire damage. If the potion is broken onto a surface or creatures, all creatures within 5’ of the target area are doused in the burning liquid. The creatures must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be hit for 2d6 fire damage. On a save, the creatures take half damage. The area continues to burn, harming all creatures who start their turn in the area or enter it for the first time for 1d4 fire damage. |
| 6 | **Potion of Goo.** | If this potion is consumed, the target creatures starts suffocating. If the potion is broken onto a creature or surface, it splatters into a transparent goo like mass that occupies the space it was thrown to. The next creature who enters that space is must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be restrained by the goo. The goo has 10 hit points, or burns away instantly with fire. |
| 7 | **Potion of Hallucinations.** | If this potion is consumed, the target creature makes a Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, they become feared to illusionary visions that surround them and follow them. Every turn the creature may attempt to break free of the visions with the same save. If the potion is broken onto a creature, the same effect can be applied. |
| 8 | **Potion of Healing I.** |  If this potion is consumed, the target creature heals for 3d4 hit points. If the potion is broken onto a creature, the targeted creature gains 1d4 hit points. |
| 9 | **Potion of Healing II.** | If this potion is ingested, the target creature heals for 5d4 hit points. If the potion is broken onto a creature, the targeted creature gains 2d4 hit points. |
| 10 | **Potion of Light.** | This potion glows with a brilliant light that sheds light in a 60 foot area, and dim light in a 30 foot area. If the potion is consumed, the creature has light leak out from their mouth, eyes, nose, and ears for 1 minute. If the potion is broken onto a surface or creatures, the area maintains the brilliant glow for 5 minutes. |
| 11 | **Potion of Perception.** | This potion heightens your senses giving you the edge in perceiving your surroundings. If the potion is consumed, the target creature gains a +2 bonus to Perception, Insight, and Investigation, plus you gain Darkvision for 20 feet. If this potion is broken on a creature or surface, no effect takes place. |
| 12 | **Potion of Performance.** | If this potion is consumed, the target gains a +1 bonus to any Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution ability checks and saving throws. If the potion is broken onto a creature or surface, nothing happens. |
| 13 | **Potion of Polymorph.** | This potion altars your anatomy rapidly. At the time of creation, choose to have the potion give the Amphibious feature, grant Darkvision for 60 ft.have the Jump spell be applied, or have the Featherfall spell be applied. If the potion is broken onto a creature or surface, nothing happens. |
| 14 | **Potion of Rejuvination.** | If this potion is consumed, the target creature restores 1 spell slot equal to their proficiency bonus. |
| 15 | **Potion of Resistances.** | If this potion is consumed or is broken onto a creature or surface, that creature or area gains resistance to fire, cold, acid, poison, and lightning damage. |
| 16 | **Potion of Senses.** | If this potion is ingested, the target creature gains Tremorsense 10 feet, Blindsense 10 feet. If the potion is broken on a creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be blinded. |
| 17 | **Potion of Smoekscreen.** | If this potion is consumed, the target creature becomes unable to speak as they cough whenever they try. If the potion is broken onto a creature or surface, it emits a cloud that acts as the spell Fog Cloud. |
| 18 | **Potion of Vanishing.** | If this potion is consumed, or broken onto a creature or object, the target has the Invisibility spell cast upon them.|
| 19 | **Potion of Volatility.** | This potion is extremely unstable and will explode at the beginning of your next turn. All creatures within 10 feet of the location this potion explodes from must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 1d10 force damage, 2d6 fire damage. On a save, creatures receive half damage. If this potion is consumed, the target creature contains the blast, but takes double the damage. |
| 20 | **Perfection.** | Choose any potion to make from the table. |
</div>


\page

## Feats

A feat represents a talent or an area of expertise that gives a character special capabilities. It em bodies training, experience, and abilities beyond what a class provides.
At certain levels, your class gives you the Ability Score Improvement feature. Using the optional feats rule, you can forgo taking that feature to take a feat of your choice instead. You can take each feat only once, unless the feat’s description says otherwise. You must meet any prerequisite specified in a feat
to take that feat. If you ever lose a feat’s prerequisite, you can’t use that feat until you regain the prerequisite.

### Aggresive Ki

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Monk*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You focus your passioniote emotions into your movements to deliver more ferocious strikes. Add half of your Strength modifier rounded up to the Ki saving throw DC. Additionally you add your Constitution Modifier in bonus damage to any Ki abilities that inflict damage.

### All Together Now

*Prerequisite: Have at least 5 level in Bard*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Through music and a face of pure determination and trust, you rally your party to fight as one. As an action, you can play an enchanting tune on your instrument to provide a series of strikes to your allies.

All allies within 25 feet who are able to perceive the melody gain a free unarmed strike. These attacks only do 1d4+Strength Modifier damage. If an ally’s attack is successful, that ally gains another free unarmed melee attack on a different target than the first one if there is such a target available.

### Ambush Expert

*Prerequisite: Have at least three levels in Rogue, or have the Soldier background*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You excel at planning guerilla warfare and taking advantage of all that is around you. As a standard action during a surprise round, you can maneuver allies for positioning before they attack. This can only be done so long as no ally within 40’ of you is already engaged in combat and allies you want to move can see you. You direct allies to move to locations within their speed that you can see with a +4 bonus to Stealth Checks as they move. After you are done directing everyone, every ally who partakes in the surprise round has an increased critical hit range of 19-20.

### Arcanic Warding

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Arcana and have the ability to cast spells*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Through your knowledge gained from tinkering with your spells, you have learned how to best defend against them. When you are targeted by a spell attack that you also have the knowledge to cast, you gain a +2 to AC against it or gain advantage on a saving throw if it uses that instead.

```
```

### Attunement to Nature

*Prerequisite: Have the class ability Wild Shape*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

With greater ease you access the magical energy of the world to transform more often. Per long rest, roll 1d4, and you gain the ability to freely Wild Shape into a 1/8 CR or lower beast while out of combat as many times as the result without expending one of your uses of Wild Shape. If you attack, cast a spell, take the help action, or take damage, you will transform back into your normal form at the end of your next turn. All rules for Wild Shape must be followed as normal.

### Blessed Heal

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Cleric*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When you cast a spell that restores Hit Points, before rolling the die you can roll a percentage die for each die that you would roll. If the result is greater than or equal to 50, you heal the maximum amount for that die. If the result is less than 50, roll the die as normal. You must finish a long rest before using Blessed Heal again.

### Delayed Reaction

You bide your time to better prep your actions with deadlier precision while watching for danger. You take a -3 on initiative rolls, but when you are the last of your allies in initiative order, during your first turn if you take the attack action you gain a +6 on all attack rolls, a +3 bonus to damage per 3 character levels, and a +1 to AC per 5 character levels until the end of your second turn.

### Devoted Prayer

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Religion*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When you pay respects to your deity, you go the extra mile. Additonal offerings, an extra verse to the usual prayer, little things that aren’t necessary but are enough that your deity appreciates your efforts. If you pray to your deity for 5 minutes after a long rest, anytime you roll a skill check, you can attempt a Religion check with a DC of (15-Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma modifier) once per long rest to reroll the skill check before the result is determined. Failing to pray at the end of a long rest will require an additional 3 long rests to be completed before this feature can be used again.

### Distracting Dance

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Performance*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

As a bonus action, you can make a Performance Check with a DC of (18-Charisma modifier) to create a small commotion focused at a creature within 30’ to allow an ally engaged in combat with the target to make a weapon attack with advantage at that moment. The target of the distraction must be able to see and hear you for this feature to work. This action acts a ranged spell attack for the purposes of any additional effects.

\page

### Eldritch Devotion

*Prerequisite: Have at least six levels in Warlock*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Your powers reach further than ever before and you broaden your horizen of abilities. Gain an additional Eldritch Invocation. Prerequisites still limit selection options of Invocations

### Expanded Magic

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Bard, Cleric, Druid, Paladin, Ranger, sorcerer, or Wizard*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

During your studies or meditations, you discover similarities and patterns between spells. Upon taking this feat, you learn one new spell from the Wizards spell list of a spell level equal to your proficiency bonus or lower. You also now know a number of bonus spells equal to your proficiency bonus.

### Fortunate Find

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Perception or Investigation*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When performing an Investigation or Perception check on an indiviual container, corpse, or item within 5 feet, you gain a +3 bonus to the check. Once every hour, you can make this roll with disadvantage with a DC of (14+Proficiency bonus) to find 1d10 gold pieces (DM's discretion)

### Gaia's Ambassador

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Animal Handling*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

There’s just something about you that intrigues animals. When you are the target of a Beast type creature’s attack, you can attempt an Animal Handling Charm check as a reaction with a save DC as listed below to charm the creature. The creature will no longer target you for its’ current attack action. If you succeed on a second Animal Handling check on the creature within five minutes of the first dissuasion check with the save DC listed below, you further Charm the creature and gain it as an ally for the 1 hour. You or an ally attacking the creature ends this effect and cannot be performed again for one day.

##### Animal Handling Check Table
| Beast Size | Save DC I |  Save DC II |
|:----:|:-------------:|:-------------:|
| Tiny  | 10 | 16 |
| Small | 14 | 20 |
|Medium| 17 | 23 |
| Large | 22 | 28 |
| Huge | 26 | 32 |
| Gargantuan | 28 | 34 |

```
```

### Gleaning Strategist

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Fighter*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

As part of a successful attack action, you can use your bonus action to gain knowledge on the creature you attack and perhaps even provide aid to others in combat against those types of foes. Roll 1d4 to determine what you gain from the attack.

| d4 | Gained benefit |
|:----:|:-------------:|
| 1  | Learn a targets current HP and AC |
| 2  | Learn a target’s vulnerabilities and immunities if any |
| 3  | Learn a targets standard attack roll bonus |
| 4  | All allies and self gain advantage on their next attack roll against the target + pick one of the other options to learn. |

### Grasshopper's Repose

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Acrobatics*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You are skilled with adding the attacks of your foes to your own movements. As a reaction, whenever a foe fails an attack roll on you with a melee attack within 5 feet and are of the same size or smaller, you may attempt an Acrobatics Check of DC (10+Target creatures attack roll) to flip over your attacker and land on the opposite side of them, gaining advantage on your next attack against them.

This can only be performed if there is at least 5 feet above the opponent and the other side of them is unoccupied. You end your maneuver 5 feet in the air and land to the floor. This movement does not trigger Attacks of Opportunity. If you fail the check, they get to make an Attack of Opportunity against you  and you do not get to move from your current location.

### Higher Ground

*Prerequisite: Have at least two level in Ranger*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

With the presence of a bird of prey, you hunt from up high. You gain a +2 to ranged attack rolls and damage rolls for when you have at least 10 feet of height advantage over a foe. These bonuses increase to +3 at 10th level.

\page

### Historian

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in History or Nature*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When you take this feat, choose a monster type to be familiar with. Whenever you can see a creature of this type, you can use your bonus action to make either a History or Nature Check against it to determine more information about it as outlined in the table below. You learn all information in the tiers below the one your check made in addition to that tier of information. This can only be attempted once per encounter.

| Nature or History check | Gained knowledge |
|:----:|:-------------:|
| 1-10  | You draw a blank and are unable to recall anything about it. |
| 11-13  | You know its speed |
| 14-16  | You know its health. |
| 17-19  | You know its AC. |
| 20+  | You know its primary method of attack and how much damage it causes or its weaknesses (choose). |



### Improved Second Wind

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Fighter*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You dig deeper within yourself to find resolve and reason to keep fighting. When you use the Second Wind Class Feature, you gain an additional 1d10 hit points. Starting at 10th level you gain 2d10 hit points, and at 15th level you gain 3d10 hit points.

### Life Charge

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Sorcerer*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Using your magic as you slay foes, you use their fleeting lives to refuel your arcane powers. Once per encounter, when you kill a creature with a spell, you may roll a d6 and on a 6 you regain 2 sorcery point. You cannot hold more than your levels permitted number of sorcery points and you cannot attempt this roll if you do not have any remaining sorcery points.

### Light Armor Master

*Prerequisite: Proficiency with Light Armor*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You are nimble enough to make use of your light armor’s bare essential protection to aid your escapes.

* Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. * While you are wearing light armor, attacks made as a reaction against you suffer disadvantage.

### Metalworking

In your free time you tend to your gear to keep them in top performance. During a Short Rest, you can use Smith’s Tools to enhance a piercing or slashing weapon. Once enhanced, the weapon will do +2 damage for 1d4 hits. If you are proficient in Smith’s Tools, this increases to 2d4 hits.

```
```

### Natural Healing

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in either Medicine, Nature, or Survival*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Through your knowledge of home remedies, you can attempt to forage your area for natural healing plants, roots, or fruit. Choose a Terrain type to be familiar with of either Arctic, Coast, Desert, Forest, Grassland, Mountains, Swamp, or Underdark. If you have Natural Explorer and are already specialized for one of the listed terrains, you may choose another from this list for this feat only.

You must succeed on a Medicine, Survival, or Nature check with a DC (18-Proficiency bonus) to successfully find ingrediants you can concoct into a healing remedy that heals for 2d4. If you have a Herbalism Kit or Alchemist Supplies this is increased to 2d8. If you are proficient with a Herbalism Kit or Alchemist Supplies you heal for 3d8 instead.

### Overwhelming Arcana

*Prerequisite: Have at least 7 levels in sorcerer*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You unblock all mental barriers you have in place to attempt a full force attack, best hope it doesn’t fizzle out and drain you instead. You may expend 7 sorcery points to cause a spell to have a 50% chance to inflict maximum damage +10 magical damage. On a fail, you roll as normal.

### One vs. One

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Barbarian*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Fully focused and unimpeded by distractions, you can unleash your full fury against a single foe. So long as no other enemy is within 5’ of you or your target, you gain a +1 to attack rolls, +1 to damage rolls, and a +1 to AC against the first attack roll against you from your target. These bonuses increase to +2 at 7th level.

### One with the Wild

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Druid*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When you use your Wild Shape Class Ability to transform into a creature of at least CR 1/2, you can add two of your hit die per three Druid levels to its’ maximum hit points. This can only be done once per long rest.

### Palace of the Mind

*Prerequisite: Have at least five levels in Monk*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Through focus and calmness, you join with the arcane forces of the world to protect yourself. When you are the target of a non-elemental damage based spell, you can add your Inteligence Modifier to your AC. Additionally, you now have a 50% chance to break the Blindness, Deafened, Paralysis, or Stunned condition on yourself at the beginning of your turn. This only occurs once per affliction per encounter.

\page

### Panic Dodge

Ignoring all planning and strategy, you obey your instincts for self preservation. Once per encounter, when a melee weapon attack would hit you, you can choose to instead drop everything in your hands and fall prone 5 feet away from the attacker, forcing them to redo their original attack against you with disadvantage.

### Past Experience

From you training and upbringing, you are more worldly than others in your position. Choose a skill to become proficient in and gain a +2 Misc. bonus to it. You gain a 2nd skill to be proficient in and gain the +2 bonus to it at 8th level, and a 3rd skill at 15th.

### Planned Arcanum

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Cleric, Druid, Paladin, or Wizard*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Through greater memorization and preperations you take, you can perform a wider variety of magic. You are able to prepare an additional number of spells equal to half of your Proficiency bonus (Minimum of 1).


### Reckless Brutality

*Prerequisite: Have at least two level in Barbarian*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

At the cost of your well being, you commit even more into your brutal attacks to seek out weak points while exposing yours. When you take this feat, your Reckless Attack grows to add a +2 to damage and increases your critical hit range to 18-20, but decreases our AC by 2 until the start of your next turn. This feature does not stack with other effects that increase your critical hit range.

### Reclaiming Invocation

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Warlock*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You gain the ability to potentially regain one of your spell slots without a rest. You can use a standard action to roll a d6 and on a 6 you regain 1 spell slot whose level is equal to your Proficiency Bonus -1 at a minimum of 1. Once you use this feature, you must finish a long rest before you can use it again.

### Reflexive Guard

In the midst of fighting, you have a heightened awareness of your surroundings. This can only activate when you are adjacent to two or more creatures that you have attacked or have attacked you during this encounter. When you are targeted by an attack, you can use your reaction to increase your AC by 3 for the next attack roll against you before your next turn.

### Reserved Power

*Prerequisite: Be able to cast spells*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

When you are left to your own devices you focus on storing arcana within yourself for later use. You gain an extra spell slot whose level is less than or equal to your spellcasting ability modifier. You cannot take a spell slot level highter than the level spells you can cast without this feat.

### Returning the Love

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Bard*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Seeing your praise and encouragement lift up your allies fills you with vigor and resolve to succeed for them. Anytime an ally succeeds on an ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes by using your Bardic Inspiration in their roll, you gain your own Bardic Inspiration die that lasts for five minutes. You can only have one Bardic Inspiration die from this feat at any time.

### Rolling Fall

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in either Athletics or Acrobatics*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Tumbling is a skill that takes practice and precision; both of which you have mastered. When you fall from a height that would normally cause you fall damage, you can attempt an Acrobatics or Athletics Check with a DC of 10 +2 per 10 feet of falling to avoid 2d6 worth of the falling damage.

### Shield Save

*Prerequisite: Be proficient in Shields*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You are skilled with the shield to such a degree that you can throw one with intense speed and accuracy to save a teammate. You can use your reaction to make an attack roll using Dexterity against a ranged attack with a DC of (8+the Attacker’s bonus to Attack Rolls), to be able to throw your shield and take the hit of the attack. This can only be done before the attack roll is determined to be successful. You must be able to see both the attacker and target of the attack, and have nothing inbetween your path to throw your shield. The shield lands 5 feet in front of the intended target. On a successful block, roll 1d8 and on an 8 your shield rebounds back to you. If the ranged attack would cause damage to an area, if this feat is successful, your shield becomes the new target location for the attack.

### Smiting Right

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Paladin*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Your connection to your deity and your bonds to the world are second to none. Once per long rest, you gain one free use of a 1st level Smite Spell without it costing a spell slot. At level 8 this increases to a 2nd level Smite Spell. Your Divine Health class ability now includes a resistance to Poison Damage and advantage on Saving Throws against Poison.

### Swift Dagger

*Prerequisite: Have at least three levels in Rogue and a Dexterity score of 18*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

You know the weight, the balance, the physics of your daggers to a deadly degree. When you make an attack with a dagger, you increase its’ base damage to 2d4 and your Critical Hit range increases to 19-20 while using one.

\page

### Wand Slinger

*Prerequisite: Have at least one level in Wizard*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Armed with two wands, you barrage your foes with more, though weaker attacks. If you are wielding one wands in each hand, you may cast 2 different cantrips that require you to make a spell attack roll using one attack action as if you were benefiting from the Multiattack feature. If you use one wand to cast a spell of 1st level or higher, the other wand cannot cast a spell.

### Smiting Right

*Prerequisite: Have at least 3 levels as a Circle of the Land Druid*
<div style='margin-top:px'></div>

Searching the mysteries of the wild has brought you to many lands outside of your home, while there you learned their secrets. You gain access to 2 spells from another spell list as described by options in Circle of the Land different from your chosen land.

### Worldly Step

Travel and exploration has granted you a comfortable air of familiarity with those lands that remain with you always. Pick 3 terrains from Arctic, Coast, Desert, Forest, Grassland, Mountains, Swamp, or Underdark to be familiar with. You no longer suffer difficult terrain while in those terrains and you gain 5 feet of movement speed while in them. additionally you have advantage on Attack Rolls and Skill Checks when you would normally be suffering from Difficult Terrain in those areas.






























\page

