## Spell Descriptions

The spells are presented in alphabetical order.


#### Air Cannon
*Evocation Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 10 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

Using both of your hands and a full breath, you extend your arms forward to assault a creature within range with an assault of air forcing the creature to make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save they are pushed 5 feet times your spellcasting ability modifier away from you and if the creature collides with a solid surface or creature, they take 1d4+1 Thunder damage for every 5 feet of remaining movement that hasn’t been used by it from the push.

If the creature collides with a second creature, the second creature must make a Str. saving throw or take half of the Thunder damage the original creature takes from being thrown. On a successful save it is only moved 5 feet and can take no damage.

If a Large creature is targeted, it is pushed back -10 feet than it normally would. A Huge or larger creature cannot be affected by this spell.

***At Higher Levels.*** The spell gains a bonus 1d4 Thunder damage to the primary target if they failed the saving throw when you reach 5th level (1d4), 11th level (2d4), and 17th level (3d4).


#### Combustion
*1st-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self (15-foot-radius)
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

You explode energy around you in a fiery fit, forcing all creatures within range to make a Dexterity saving throw or start burning. On a failed save, the creature takes 1d8 fire damage and is burned, or only take half damage and are not burned on a successful saving throw. Burning creatures take 1d8 fire damage at the start of their turn and can make a Constitution saving throw at the end of its turn. On a successful save, the burning ends for it.

This spell evolves and gains the effects of Flaming Breeze if you use cast Air Cannon before this spell on the same turn, and evolves and gains the effects of Magmatic Force if you cast Earthen Pillar before this spell on the same turn.

***Flaming Breeze*** If you cast Air Cannon before using this spell on the same turn, your fire rushes out from you as a wall of flaming air, changing this spell’s casting to a spell attack roll with advantage against all creatures within range. Creatures who you successfully attack are hurt for 1d8 fire damage and are burned. Burning creatures take 1d8 fire damage at the start of their turn and can make a Constitution saving throw at the end of its turn. On a successful save, the burning ends for it.

***Magmatic Force***  If you cast Earthen Pillar before using this spell on the same turn, your pillar gains molten cracks and explodes at the end of your turn if it is within range of this attack. Creatures restrained by the pillar take 1d8 fire damage, and then they proceed to fall. Creatures not restrained by the pillar, but within 5 feet of it when it explodes must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures take 1d8 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful save.

**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the burning damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 1st.


#### Crag Dome
*1st-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** S, V, 5 cubic feet of stone*
- **Duration:** 1 minute

You create a net shaped dome of earth around you to act as your guard. This grants you three-quarters cover to all sources of attacks for the duration and a damage reduction of 1d4. While within the dome, you cannot cast spells that require a Somatic component. The dome has 20 hit points, and takes half the damage you do for successful attacks against you. When it drops to 0 hit points, it crumbles away.

You can gather your dome together into a sphere as a bonus action and lob it to any point you can see within 20 feet. All creatures within 5 feet of the chosen location must make a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures take half of the remaining health of dome as bludgeoning damage on a failed saving , or none on a successful save. If your dome previously had ice or fire properties fused into it, add 1d6 damage of the relative type to this attack.

This spell evolves into Glacial Dome if you cast Ice Shards after this spell on the same turn, and evolves into Molten Cage if you cast Flaring Mote after this spell on the same turn.

***Glacial Dome*** If you cast Ice Shards after this spell on the same turn, Your Crag Dome gains a layer of magical ice stalagmites onto it, imposing disadvantage on attacks from foes attacking within 5 feet of the dome.

***Molten Cage*** If you cast Flaring Mote on the same turn as this spell, your dome glows with fire born within the rock. Any creature who attacks you or your dome from within 10 feet takes 1d4+1 fire damage.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the hit points of the dome increases by 1d10 for each slot level above 1st.

\page

#### Desperate Salvation
*2nd-level Abjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 reaction, which you take when an ally you can see within range is hit by an attack.
- **Range:** 80 feet
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 round

You bless a creature you can see within range with temporary salvation. When a creature you can see in range is damaged by an attack, they gain 2d4 + spellcasting ability modifier temporary hit points. 

***At higher levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the temporary hit points increases by 1d4 for each slot level above 1st.


#### Earthen Pillar
*Evocation Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** S, V, 5 cubic feet of stone*
- **Duration:** 1 minute

Using stone either on the floor, the walls, or the ceiling, you can create a pillar up to 15 feet tall and 5 feet in diameter that juts outward. The area where a pillar appears must be wide enough for its diameter, and you can target the ground under a creature if that creature is Medium or smaller.

The pillar has 30 hit points and when reduced to 0 hit points, a pillar crumbles into rubble, which creates an area of difficult terrain within a 5-foot-radius that lasts until the rubble is cleared. Each 5-foot-diameter portion of the area requires at least 1 minute to clear by hand.

If a pillar is created under a creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures are lifted by the pillar on a failed save, or they move to an unoccupied space within 5 feet on a successful save. A creature can choose to fail the save.

If a pillar is prevented from reaching its full height because of a ceiling or other obstacle, a creature on the pillar takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage and is Restrained between the pillar and the obstacle. The restrained creature can use an action to make a Strength or Dexterity check (the creature’s choice) against your spell save DC. On a success, the creature is no longer restrained and falls from it.

***At Higher Levels*** The pillars max length increases by 5 feet when you reach 5th level (20 feet), 11th level (25 feet), and 17th level (30 feet).

```
```
#### Eldritch Blight
*2nd-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 60 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous 

You curse a target and crack the ground beneath them to summon forth eldritch fire that throws them into the sky. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, it inflicts 1d10 fire damage and 1d10 force damage, and they must succeed on a Strength saving throw. The creature is thrown 10 feet into the air on a failed save, and resist being thrown into the air on a successful save.

***At higher levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the blast launches the target an additional 10 feet into the air per spell slot level over 2nd level.


#### Essence Transfer
*1st-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 20 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous 

You tap into the very life essence of two creatures within range and meddle with their well being by plucking at their life strings. You may attempt to transfer 2d8 Hit Points from one target to another within range.

If both targets are willing, the transfer occurs. If one or both creatures are unwilling, they must succeed on a Constitution saving throw. The transfer occurs if all unwilling creatures fail their save, and the spell fails if an unwilling creature successfully saves. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.

***At higher levels*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the hit points transfered increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 1st.

\page

#### Flaring Mote
*Evocation Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 minute (Concentration) 

You breathe deeply and create a floating mote of fire within 5 feet of you that cannot be put out by non-magical means. It gives off a bright light in a 15 foot radius, and dim light for an additional 15 feet past that. The mote can be moved up to 30 feet as a bonus action, and can finish its movement occupying the same square as another creature. If a creature starts its turn within the same square as the mote of fire, they take 1d6+1 fire damage.

As an action, you can explode the mote, forcing all creatures within 5 feet of it to make a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures take 3d4 fire damage on a failed save, and half damage on a successful saveOn a fail, they take 3d4 fire damage. On a save, they take half damage. You cannot be hurt by this fire.

The explosion damage of this spell increases by 1d4 when you reach 5th level (4d4), 11th level (5d4), and 17th level (6d4)


#### Grasping vision
*2nd-level Enchantment*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 15 feet
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

Make a ranged spell attack against a creature as you send them captivating sights of your dieties greatness. The creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become Restrained by your deities glory. 

An affected creature may attempt to break free of this vision by making a Wisdom saving throw at the end of its turn. On a successful save, it is no loner restrained and this spell will not affect it again for 24 hours.


#### Ice Shards
*Evocation Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self (10-feet-radius)
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

You can freeze water in the air into sharp needles made of ice and burst them outwards, causing more damage the closer they are to you. All creatures within range must make a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures within 5 feet of you take 2d4 cold damage, and creatures 10 feet away take half that damage on a failed save.

The damage increases by 2d4 when you reach 5th level (4d4), 11th level (6d4), and 17th level (8d4).

