#### Improved Mage Hand
*Conjuration Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** 1 minute (concentration)

A spectral, floating hand appears at a point you choose within range. The hand lasts for the duration or until you dismiss it as an action. The hand vanishes if it is ever more than 30 feet away from you or if you cast this spell again.

You can use your action to control the hand. You can use the hand to manipulate an object, open an unlocked door or container, stow or retrieve an item from an open container, or pour the contents out of a vial. You can move the hand up to 30 feet each time you use it.

As part of the creation of this hand, you can use the hand to make 2 melee spell attacks against a creature within 5 feet of the hand. On a hit, the target takes Force damage equal to 1d6 + your Strength modifier. You can repeat this as an action on your subsequent turns. The hand dissapears after 2 successful hits.

The hand also can now carry 20 pounds and can be used to perform the Shove and Trip action. The hand uses your Strength modifier for any Strength checks it makes against a creature.

***At Higher Levels.*** The spells damage increases by 1d6 when you reach at 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).


#### Intoxication
*2nd-level Enchantment*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 15 feet
- **Components:** S, V, M (Alchol worth 10 gp, which the spell consumes)
- **Duration:** 10 minutes (concentration)

Taking a large drink from an alcoholic beverage, you amplify and spread the effects from you to others. All creatures within range must make a Constitution saving throw. Creatures become drunk on a failed save, and gain the following effects

* Gain 5 temporary hit points.
* Gain advantage on Strength ability checks.
* Have advantage to saving throws against Fear.
* Have disadvantage on Wisdom saving throws.
* Have disadvantage on Intelligence and Wisdom ability checks.


\page

#### Overload
*9th-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 120 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

You hone within as much elemental magic as you can butstill it leaks forth from you as if it were lightning before unleashing it in a powerful ray of white and orange light. Make a ranged spell attack against one creature within range and barrage them with a concentrated beam made of the purest, and most condensed form of each element. Ton a hit, the creature takes 4d10 Thunder, 4d10 Cold, 4d10 Bludgeoning, and 4d10 Fire damage.

Creatures damaged by this spell become vulnerable to Bludgeoning, Cold, Fire, and Thunder damage for 1 minute. This spell is so taxing that it cannot be affected by Metamagic.


#### Penance Smite
*3rd-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 minute (Concentration)

Penance Smite

With the blessing of your deity and a prayer of power, you bestow onto a creature an enlightening fate. The next time you hit a creature with an unarmed strike before this spell ends, the creature starts glowing with the light of your deity.

At the start of their next turn, they are smited by a light appearing above them that covers a 15-foot cube centered on them. All creatures within the light must make a Dexterity saving throw or be hit for 3d6 radiant damage. The original target automatically fails this saving throw.

If a target hit by this attack is undead, they take an extra 1d6 radiant damage. The caster of this spell is immune to the damage from this spell.


#### Red Dawn
*3rd-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** (Self) 20-foot-radius
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

Fire spews from your hands to the sky and blankets above until only the fire is visible. Create a blanket of fire 50 feet above you that stretches out in a 20-foot radius. This fire doesn’t fall and inflict damage until the beginning of your next turn. Those caught in the flames cannot avoid them and take 5d8 fire damage.

***At higher levels*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 3rd.

