#### Relentless Taunt
*2nd-level Enchantment*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** 1 minute (Concentration)

Using wit and a bit of magical effects for emphasis, you construct an infuriating insult to a creature in range that taunts it into a loathing fixation on you. The target must succeed on a Charisma saving throw or become unable to willingly move away from you and can not take any standard action, bonus action, or reaction, that does not include you as a target.

If the creature cannot see you at the beginning of its turn, the spell ends. 

***At higher levels*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.


#### Spectral Ammo
*1st-level Enchantment*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V, M (A tree nut or fruit)
- **Duration:** 1 minute

When you cast this spell, the next piece of ammo that you fire from a bow or crossbow becomes slightly transparant and glows with a slight purple light. This attack ignores a creatures bonus recieved from cover and armor, and adds 1d6 force damage.

***At higher levels*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the force damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.


#### Spirit Puppet
*2nd-level Conjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** S, V, M (a fresh drop of blood, which the spell consumes)
- **Duration:** 1 minute

Using blood that is no more than 1 minute old from your intended target creature, you conjure a small phantasmic puppet that loosesly resembles your target within 5 feet. The puppet has 4d8 hit points and automatically fails all saving throws. This puppet disappears at the start of your next turn or when it's hit points are reduced to 0. This puppet is magically linked to the target and any damage or healing this puppet sustains is also given to the target provided they are within 60’.

The puppet is resistant to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage from non-magical weapons, cannot be given a condition, and cannot be moved from where it is conjured.

Creatures can share a space with the phantom puppet. If a creature shares a space with the phantom puppet, the phantom cannot be targeted but will still be hit with area of effect damage.


\page


#### Stunning Shot
*1st-level Transmutation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V, M (the seed of a flower)
- **Duration:** 1 minute

You magically grow a poison pollen flower onto an arrow or bolt you are holding that lasts for 1 minute. If this bolt or arrow successfully damages a creature, the pollen explodes out inflicting 1d4 additional poison damage and they must succeed on a Constitution saving throw. The creature becomes Stunned until the start of your next turn on a failed save, or have their movement reduced by 5 feet on a succssful save.

Creatures immune to poison are immune to the stun as well.

#### Sweeping Wave
*1st-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self (30-foot cone)
- **Components:** S, V, M (4 liters of water)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

You cast forth a conjured wave of icy water that buffets creatures, forcing them to make a Dexterity saving throw. Creatures take 2d8 cold damage on a failed save, and the creature closest to you that failed their save is knocked prone. Creatures take half damage on a successful save. This wave also snuffs out non magical fire that is not being carried by a creature.


This spell evolves and gains the effects of Hurricane Tide if you use cast Air Cannon before this spell on the same turn, and evolves and gains the effects of Marshland Burial if you cast Earthen Pillar before this spell on the same turn.

***Hurricane Tide.*** If you cast Air Cannon before using this spell, your Sweeping Wave pushes Medium or smaller creatures back 1d4 times 5 feet, and they take 1d4 +1 Thunder damage.

***Marshland Burial.*** If you cast Earthen Pillar before using this spell and it is targeted as part of this attack, your Sweeping Wave fuses with it to create muddy mote of difficult terrain in a 10-foot-radius to the pillar that pulls in creatures within range. A creature who failed their saving throw and is within the pillars difficult terrain is Restrained by mud until the start of our next turn.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the waves damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 1st.

