```

#### Temporal Pulse
*enchantment Cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 15 foot cone
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

You launch a pulsing shock waves at a target that disrupts their bodily functions. Make a ranged spell attack on each creature in range. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 Thunder damage, and its speed is reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn.

The damage of this spell increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8)


#### Ties of Life
*2nd-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1  action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

Targeting an ally within range, you reach out to their life force with yours. You combine your current HP with theirs and divide it back amongst the 2 of you as equally as you can. Until the start of your next turn, you both take damage for any damage the other suffers but also both gain +1 AC. If the ally is unwilling, this spell fails.


#### Tornado
*1st-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self (5-foot-radius)
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** 2 Rounds


You swirl up a tornado underneath you, causing you to hover and granting you protection that moves with you. Until the spell ends, you gain the following effects:

* You gain 10 feet of movement speed.
* You ignore non-magical difficult terrain.
* You cannot be targeted for an attack of opportunity that would be made from within 5 feet of the tornado.
* Ranged weapon attacks against you have disadvantage.


This spell evolves and gains the effects of Tundra Assault if you use cast Ice Shards after this spell on the same turn, and evolves and gains the effects of Infernal Winds if you cast Flaming Mote after this spell on the same turn.

***Tundra Assault.*** If you cast Ice Shards after using this spell, your tornado also gains the ice needles, carrying them as you move. Any creatures excluding you who start their turn within 5ft. of the Tornado or enter its area for the first time are subject to 2d4 cold damage and have their movement speed reduced by 5 feet.


***Infernal Winds.*** If you cast Flaring Mote after using this spell, your Tornado ignites with flames. Any creature who starts their turn within 5ft. of the tornado or enters its area for the first time take 2d4 fire damage. If a creature ends its turn within the tornados range, they take 2d4 fire damage.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the gained movement speed increases by 10 feet for each spell slot level above 1st.

\page

#### Unification
*4th-level Enchantment*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 120 feet
- **Components:** S, V
- **Duration:** 5 minutes (Concentration)

Focusing on yourself and your allies, you can link everyones souls together and everyone effected has the doors of possibility opened to them. You can target a number of creatures equal to your Charisma modifier to gain the following effects:

* All creatures affected by this spell can communicate telepathically with one another, but still require a shared language to be understood.
* Any creature can cast a spell owned by another creature that doesn't require material components, using their own statistics for the casting, but using the owner of the spell's spell slots
* Any healing applied to one of the creatures can be given to any other affected creature instead.

An unwilling creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw to not be linked via this spell.


#### Zealous Betrayal
*3rd-level Illusion*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 40 feet
- **Components:** S, V, M (A silver ring worth 10 gp, which the spell consumes)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

With the mischevous intent of a devil, you whisper words of temptation towards a target you can see within range and force it to make a Wisdom saving throw. The creature becomes Charmed with intense emotions and uses its strongest melee attack on the closest creature to it if there is one in range on a failed save. On a successful save, the creature knows you tried to charm it, and gains advantage on Wisdom saving throws until the end of your next turn.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, The creature gains a +1 bonus to their attack roll against their target for each spell slot level above 3rd.

