```
#### Zwendyll's Blade
*5th-level Transmutation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** S, V, M (A ravens feather, a metal key, and a shell from the sea)
- **Duration:** 5 minutes (concentration)

Summoning forth the forces from the the Infinite Layers of the Abyss, you create in your hands a morphing, obsidion blade that distorts the reality around it. When using this weapon, make a touch spell attack against the target. On a hit, the creature takes 3d6 psychic damage, and they must roll a d10 as a distortion from the Infinitie Layers of the Abyss touches them. All lingering effects last until the end of the creatures next turn.

##### Zwendyll's Blade Effect
| d10 | Effect |
|:----:|:-------------|
| 1  | The creature becomes partially transparent, dealing and taking half damage |
| 2  | The creature is teleported 10 feet in a random direction |
| 3  | The creature is polymorphed into a Maw Demon |
| 4  | The creature is partially torn in half, and then stitched back, taking 2d6 psychic damage|
| 5  | The creature grows wings and horns, granting a fly speed of 15 ft. and a +1 attack roll bonus to unarmed strikes 
| 6  | The creature is unable to tell friend from foe and considers all creatures as hostile enemies|
| 7  | The creature loses any ability to cast spells |
| 8  | The creature is Restrained and rapidly teleports back and forth from the Material plane and the Ethereal plane, becoming unable to target any creature for an action and not being able to be targeted with any type of actions. |
| 9  | The creature swaps places with the closest creature that isn't the attacker. Make a new attack roll against this creature with advantage. |
| 10 | The creature resists the distortions  |
